# ORIG TITLE    Italian police seize 1.3 billion euros from Sicilian man . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Over 1.3 billion euros in cash and property has been seized by Italian police from one person. It was taken from Vito Nicastri, a Sicilian alternative energy entrepreneur who has alleged ties to the mafia. He is accused of tax evasion; allegedly he did not declare all of the value of his businesses. The seizures include 43 companies, 98 pieces of real estate and 66 bank accounts. 
